---
/*
 * Social Media Monitoring — deep dive on Platform Capability 03.
 * Expands the "Social Media Monitoring" section of src/pages/platform.astro
 * into a full page: platforms monitored, what we detect, confidence
 * scoring, handle-permutation methodology, evidence collection for
 * takedowns, a per-platform capability table, and a closing CTA.
 */
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Social Media Monitoring — Averrow"
  description="Averrow's Digital Risk Protection platform monitors six social platforms for impersonation, handle squatting, and executive spoofing, with evidence for takedowns."
>
  <section class="sm-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sm-hero-eyebrow">Platform / Social Media Monitoring</div>
      <h1>Impersonation moves<br /><span class="sm-hero-accent">faster than your brand team.</span></h1>
      <p>
        Averrow watches six platforms around the clock for fake accounts, handle squatting,
        and executive impersonation &mdash; then scores every finding so your team only
        reviews what actually warrants a takedown.
      </p>
      <div class="sm-status-panel" aria-label="Live social monitoring status">
        <div class="sm-status-panel-label">
          <span class="sm-status-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          Monitoring Status &mdash; All Platforms Active
        </div>
        <div class="sm-status-grid">
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">Twitter/X</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">LinkedIn</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">Instagram</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">TikTok</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">GitHub</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
          <div class="sm-status-row"><span class="sm-status-name">YouTube</span><span class="sm-status-state">SCANNING</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="sm-nav">
    <div class="sm-nav-inner">
      <a href="#detect" class="sm-tab active">What We Detect</a>
      <a href="#scoring" class="sm-tab">Confidence Scoring</a>
      <a href="#permutation" class="sm-tab">Handle Permutation</a>
      <a href="#evidence" class="sm-tab">Evidence Collection</a>
      <a href="#platforms" class="sm-tab">Platform Coverage</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="sm-section" id="detect">
    <div class="sm-row">
      <div class="sm-text">
        <div class="section-label">What We Detect</div>
        <h2>Four ways impersonation shows up on social.</h2>
        <p>
          Attackers don&rsquo;t need to touch your infrastructure to damage your brand &mdash;
          a convincing handle is often enough. Averrow auto-discovers your real brand
          accounts from your company website, then watches for anything imitating them.
          Register your named executives too, and the same handle-based detection runs
          on their identities.
        </p>
        <ul class="sm-features">
          <li><strong>Impersonation accounts</strong> &mdash; fake profiles built to look like your brand, a product, or a support channel</li>
          <li><strong>Handle squatting</strong> &mdash; your brand name or close variants registered and held, claimed or unclaimed</li>
          <li><strong>Executive impersonation</strong> &mdash; register your leadership team by name once; Averrow generates the handles an attacker would use to impersonate them, checks all six platforms, and flags matches that aren&rsquo;t your executives&rsquo; own official accounts</li>
          <li><strong>Unauthorized brand usage</strong> &mdash; logo abuse and brand-keyword misuse in handles and profile content</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="sm-visual">
        <div class="sm-detect-grid">
          <div class="sm-detect-card">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M4 21v-1a8 8 0 0 1 16 0v1"/><line x1="2" y1="2" x2="22" y2="22"/></svg>
            <div class="sm-detect-name">Impersonation Accounts</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sm-detect-card">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="10" rx="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 9.9-1"/></svg>
            <div class="sm-detect-name">Handle Squatting</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sm-detect-card">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21l-2-2"/></svg>
            <div class="sm-detect-name">Executive Impersonation</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sm-detect-card">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2l2.4 6.6L21 11l-6.6 2.4L12 20l-2.4-6.6L3 11l6.6-2.4z"/></svg>
            <div class="sm-detect-name">Unauthorized Brand Usage</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-section" id="scoring">
    <div class="sm-row reversed">
      <div class="sm-text">
        <div class="section-label">How It Works</div>
        <h2>Multi-signal confidence scoring, not a keyword match.</h2>
        <p>
          A handle containing your brand name &mdash; or your CEO&rsquo;s name &mdash; isn&rsquo;t
          automatically a threat: fan accounts and press mentions exist too. Averrow weighs
          name-similarity and handle-construction signals together to produce a confidence
          score, so your team reviews a short, ranked list instead of every mention on
          the internet.
        </p>
        <ul class="sm-features">
          <li>Name similarity between the handle/display name and your registered brand or executive name</li>
          <li>Handle-permutation match &mdash; found using one of the exact variants an impersonator would register (separator swaps, &ldquo;official&rdquo;/&ldquo;support&rdquo; suffixes, character substitution)</li>
          <li>Brand-keyword usage in the handle itself</li>
          <li>Cross-reference against your registered official handles, so your own accounts and executives are never flagged</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="callout">Findings are cross-correlated with everything else Averrow already knows about your brand &mdash; a squatted handle linked to a phishing domain in the same feed cycle escalates automatically.</div>
        <p>
          Executive impersonation runs on this same name/handle matching &mdash; entirely
          deterministic, with no photo, bio, or follower analysis involved. Register an
          executive once and Averrow checks all six platforms on an ongoing basis for
          handles that could pass as them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="sm-visual">
        <div class="sm-score-eyebrow">Illustrative Example &mdash; Flagged Profile</div>
        <div class="sm-score-card">
          <div class="sm-score-card-row"><span>Handle</span><span class="sm-mono">@yourbrand_support</span></div>
          <div class="sm-score-card-row"><span>Platform</span><span class="sm-mono">Twitter/X</span></div>
          <div class="sm-score-card-row"><span>Name similarity</span><span class="sm-mono">92%</span></div>
          <div class="sm-score-card-row sm-score-card-last"><span>Handle construction</span><span class="sm-mono">Brand + &ldquo;_support&rdquo; suffix</span></div>
          <div class="sm-score-verdict">
            <div class="sm-score-verdict-label">Confidence</div>
            <div class="sm-score-verdict-value">Likely Impersonation</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-section" id="permutation">
    <div class="sm-row">
      <div class="sm-text">
        <div class="section-label">Methodology</div>
        <h2>Handle permutation generation.</h2>
        <p>
          Averrow doesn&rsquo;t wait for a lookalike account to be reported &mdash; it generates
          the plausible variants an attacker would register and checks each one across all
          six platforms, on an ongoing basis.
        </p>
        <ul class="sm-features">
          <li><strong>Separator variations</strong> &mdash; underscores, dots, and dashes inserted into your brand handle</li>
          <li><strong>Suffix/prefix additions</strong> &mdash; official, HQ, team, support, and similar terms appended or prepended</li>
          <li><strong>Character substitution</strong> &mdash; visually similar characters swapped in (0 for o, 1 for l, rn for m)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="sm-visual">
        <div class="sm-perm-eyebrow">Example Permutations &mdash; illustrative, not a real brand</div>
        <div class="sm-perm-source">yourbrand</div>
        <div class="sm-perm-grid">
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">your_brand</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">your.brand</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">your-brand</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">yourbrandhq</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">official_yourbrand</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">yourbrandteam</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">y0urbrand</span>
          <span class="sm-perm-chip">yourbrand_support</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-section" id="evidence">
    <div class="sm-row reversed">
      <div class="sm-text">
        <div class="section-label">Takedowns</div>
        <h2>Evidence, packaged for the platform&rsquo;s abuse team.</h2>
        <p>
          A takedown request that arrives with context moves faster. Every flagged account
          carries an automatically-assembled record your team can attach directly to a
          platform abuse report.
        </p>
        <ul class="sm-features">
          <li>Handle, platform, profile URL, and detection timestamp captured automatically</li>
          <li>The confidence score and the exact signals that produced it</li>
          <li>Cross-references to related threats seen elsewhere &mdash; domains, email, other platforms</li>
          <li>Analyst classification notes, ready to attach to a takedown submission</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="sm-visual">
        <div class="sm-evidence-eyebrow">Evidence Package Contents</div>
        <div class="sm-evidence-list">
          <div class="sm-evidence-item"><span class="sm-evidence-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Handle, display name, profile URL, and capture timestamp</div>
          <div class="sm-evidence-item"><span class="sm-evidence-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Confidence score + contributing signals</div>
          <div class="sm-evidence-item"><span class="sm-evidence-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Related threat cross-references</div>
          <div class="sm-evidence-item sm-evidence-last"><span class="sm-evidence-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Analyst classification notes</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-platforms" id="platforms">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center;">Platform Coverage</div>
      <h2 class="sm-platforms-h2">What Averrow Checks, Per Platform</h2>
      <p class="sm-platforms-p">Every platform gets handle checking and impersonation scanning. Permutation checking and evidence generation are close behind &mdash; YouTube&rsquo;s more limited handle namespace makes permutation checking partial today.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sm-table-wrap">
      <table class="sm-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Platform</th>
            <th>Handle Check</th>
            <th>Impersonation Scan</th>
            <th>Permutation Check</th>
            <th>Evidence</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Twitter/X</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>LinkedIn</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Instagram</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>TikTok</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>GitHub</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>YouTube</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td><td class="sm-partial">Partial</td><td class="sm-yes">&#10003;</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-related">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center;">Keep Exploring</div>
      <h2 class="sm-related-h2">The Rest of the Platform</h2>
      <div class="sm-related-grid">
        <a href="/platform/threat-detection" class="sm-related-card">
          <div class="sm-related-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"/></svg></div>
          <div class="sm-related-name">Threat Detection</div>
          <div class="sm-related-desc">Continuous monitoring across phishing, domains, and threat feeds.</div>
        </a>
        <a href="/platform/email-security" class="sm-related-card">
          <div class="sm-related-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg></div>
          <div class="sm-related-name">Email Security</div>
          <div class="sm-related-desc">SPF, DKIM, DMARC, and MX graded A+ through F.</div>
        </a>
        <a href="/platform/ai-agents" class="sm-related-card">
          <div class="sm-related-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="3" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="14" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="3" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/><rect x="14" y="14" width="7" height="7" rx="1"/></svg></div>
          <div class="sm-related-name">The Agent Mesh</div>
          <div class="sm-related-desc">How 42 AI agents fuse social signals into one exposure score.</div>
        </a>
        <a href="/platform/campaign-intelligence" class="sm-related-card">
          <div class="sm-related-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="2.5"/><circle cx="18" cy="6" r="2.5"/><circle cx="12" cy="18" r="2.5"/><line x1="8" y1="7.5" x2="10.5" y2="16"/><line x1="16" y1="7.5" x2="13.5" y2="16"/><line x1="8.5" y1="6" x2="15.5" y2="6"/></svg></div>
          <div class="sm-related-name">Campaign Intelligence</div>
          <div class="sm-related-desc">Threats that share infrastructure, connected into a single campaign.</div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="sm-related-back"><a href="/platform">&larr; Back to Platform Overview</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sm-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>See who&rsquo;s impersonating your brand on social right now.</h2>
      <p>Run a free exposure scan in under five minutes &mdash; no signup, no credit card.</p>
      <div class="sm-cta-actions">
        <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Demo</a>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline">Run a Free Scan</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── HERO ── */
  .sm-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--gradient-hero);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .sm-hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--amber);
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .sm-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.6vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .sm-hero-accent { color: var(--amber); }
  .sm-hero p {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── STATUS PANEL ── */
  .sm-status-panel {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--glass-card-bg);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(160%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(160%);
    text-align: left;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .sm-status-panel-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .sm-status-dot {
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--green);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(60,184,120,0.55);
    animation: sm-pulse 1.8s ease-out infinite;
  }
  @keyframes sm-pulse {
    0%   { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(60,184,120,0.55); }
    70%  { box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(60,184,120,0); }
    100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(60,184,120,0); }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .sm-status-dot { animation: none; box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(60,184,120,0.2); }
  }
  .sm-status-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 8px 16px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .sm-status-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
  }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .sm-status-row { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.025); }
  .sm-status-name { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .sm-status-state { color: var(--green-text); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .sm-status-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  @media (max-width: 480px) { .sm-status-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  /* ── SUB NAV ── */
  .sm-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 64px;
    z-index: 50;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .sm-nav {
    background: rgba(248,247,245,0.8);
    border-bottom-color: rgba(226,221,213,0.5);
  }
  .sm-nav-inner {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .sm-tab {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .sm-tab:hover,
  .sm-tab.active {
    background: var(--accent-bg);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  /* ── CAPABILITY SECTIONS ── */
  .sm-section { padding: 3rem 0; position: relative; }
  .sm-section:nth-of-type(odd) { background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-primary) 0%, var(--bg-secondary) 100%); }
  .sm-section:nth-of-type(even) { background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-secondary) 0%, var(--bg-tertiary) 100%); }
  .sm-row {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .sm-row.reversed { direction: rtl; }
  .sm-row.reversed > * { direction: ltr; }
  .sm-text h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 36px);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .sm-text p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .sm-features {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .sm-features li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .sm-features li::before {
    content: "\2713";
    color: var(--green);
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .sm-features li strong { color: var(--text-primary); }
  .callout {
    background: var(--accent-bg);
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,60,60,0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .sm-visual {
    background: rgba(14,26,43,0.55);
    border: 1px solid rgba(120,160,200,0.12);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.2), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
  }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .sm-visual {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    border-color: rgba(26,31,46,0.08);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.06), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
  }

  /* Detect grid */
  .sm-detect-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.85rem; }
  .sm-detect-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--amber);
  }
